  <p>Block 4 places Chennai in its watershed context and introduces the <strong>NE monsoon</strong> as the dominant driver of surface change in the region. Students identify the major watersheds around Chennai (Adyar, Cooum, Kosasthalaiyar, Buckingham Canal) and trace how monsoon variability shapes the city's flood and drought cycle. Exit: predict one consequence of monsoon variability for a Chennai location of your choosing.</p>
